webpackJsonp([0xbca6abe1c1ce],{9045:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Explaining the Unexplainable",date:"11 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-11-explaining-the-unexplainable/",tags:"Y2002"},html:'<p>Alwin writes about <a href="http://www.vfth.com/2002/04/10#NTo0MTowOSBQTQdbdb">talkng about the Halocaust with his daughter</a>, finding it better to turn off the TV program that started the discussion. It reminded me of the <a href="http://www.bergenbelsen.de/index_E.htm">Memorial at Bergen-Belsen</a>, less than an hour\'s drive from us, which is so moving precisely because there is nothing to see. The camp was burnt down by the British just weeks after it was liberated. Today it\'s just a field with mounds, a couple dozen in all. Each mound is a mass grave. Each mound represents tens of thousands of victims. The last time we were there, it was a cloudy, gloomy day, and we could hear gunfire from nearby troops on exercise. Eerie.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Changing Professions",date:"11 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-11-changing-professions/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Germany in the Spring and Jiang Zemin",date:"12 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-12-germany-in-the-spring-and-jiang-zemin/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Changing Professions",date:"11 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-11-changing-professions/",tags:"Y2002"},html:'<p>Another note for Alwin, who <a href="http://www.vfth.com/2002/04/10#MzowOTo0OSBQTQdbdb">did a day of day care yesterday</a>. "...these kids were cared for an entire day by two experienced RNs with years of parenting experience. We could charge what it\'s worth, but who could afford to pay?"</p>\n<p>Our "Tagesmütter" (translates as "day mother", the dry translation is "in-home day care provider") (there are also "Tagesväter" but they are rare...) has 20 years of professional experience, she teaches and certifies in-home day care providers, founded the state board and is on the national board of in-home day care, and is politically active on the national level on behalf of her profession. (And when she\'s out politicking, she arranges a substitute at no charge.) Her hourly rate is 25 cents per hour higher than average.</p>\n<p>Just so you know what you could expect if you change professions :-)</p>\n<p>(Also posted in his <a href="http://www.vfth.com/discuss/msgReader$1857">discussion group</a>)</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Yet Another PHP Referers Script",date:"10 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-10-yet-another-php-referers-script/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Explaining the Unexplainable",date:"11 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-11-explaining-the-unexplainable/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Yet Another PHP Referers Script",date:"10 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-10-yet-another-php-referers-script/",tags:"Y2002"},html:'<p><a href="http://davespicks.com">Dave\'s Picks</a> has yet another way to <a href="http://davespicks.com/writing/programming/last10refs.html">display referrers</a> with PHP. No database required.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Bayern Madrid vs Real Munich",date:"10 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-10-bayern-madrid-vs-real-munich/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Changing Professions",date:"11 Apr 2002",slug:"/2002-04-11-changing-professions/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:904,pageCount:1101}}}});
